TITLE: What we know about the armed bystander who killed the shooter at an Indiana mall
SUMMARY: Dressed in shorts and a T-shirt, Elisjsha Dicken was shopping with his girlfriend when a gunman opened fire on a food court at a Greenwood, Indiana, mall Sunday evening, killing three people and wounding two others.

TITLE: UK smashes its hottest-day record, 100 million Americans under alerts in global heat emergency
SUMMARY: Heat waves across multiple continents have dashed records, threatened public health and bucked infrastructure, in what scientists say are signs of the climate crisis' impact on day-to-day weather.

TITLE: National Archives asks Homeland Security to explain potentially deleted Secret Service texts
SUMMARY: The National Archives has joined a growing list of federal agencies and officials demanding answers about a batch of missing text messages from the US Secret Service from January 5 and 6, 2021, that may have been deleted.

TITLE: 'Many more people would have died': Armed bystander killed gunman who had 3 guns and 100 rounds of ammunition, police say
SUMMARY: The gunman who killed three people and injured two others at a mall in Greenwood, Indiana, Sunday evening was armed with two rifles, a Glock pistol and more than 100 rounds of ammunition, police said.

TITLE: Opinion: The Secret Service's actions on text messages don't pass the smell test
SUMMARY: Arick Wierson, a former government IT official, writes whatever happened to the deleted Secret Service text messages from January 6 does not quite pass the smell test. Though the Secret Service maintains the deleted text messages were not a part of any sort of malicious plan, that's a hard explanation to fathom.

TITLE: Judge orders October trial for lawsuit between Elon Musk and Twitter
SUMMARY: In an early victory for Twitter, a judge on Tuesday ruled that the company's lawsuit against Elon Musk over their $44 billion acquisition agreement should go to a five-day trial in October.

TITLE: Why women do or don't change their name when they get married
SUMMARY: Despite increased gender equality, about 20% to 30% of women retain their own surname. This decision is influenced by economic, social, romantic and religious factors -- especially when kids are involved.

TITLE: CNN Poll: Most voters say neither Republican nor Democratic congressional candidates have the right priorities
SUMMARY: Neither Republican nor Democratic candidates for Congress are seen by most voters as having the right priorities, according to a new CNN poll conducted by SSRS. The survey finds voters closely divided in their preference for this year's midterm elections and on the potential consequences of a Republican victory.

TITLE: Want to study Harry Styles? Consider this upcoming college course
SUMMARY: Texas State University will offer a spring 2023 course titled "Harry Styles and the Cult of Celebrity: Identity, the Internet and European Pop Culture." The class will explore Styles' fame and the influence of social media, among other themes.

TITLE: The real reason Donald Trump is on board with LIV Golf
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is not one to quibble about ethics when money is on the line.

TITLE: Drew Barrymore wants us to all go out in the rain and enjoy
SUMMARY: Drew Barrymore is in a real life rom-com with the rain.

TITLE: Starbucks may not be done closing stores over safety concerns
SUMMARY: Starbucks may not be done closing stores over safety concerns.

TITLE: Another company called Meta says Facebook rebrand 'obliterated' its business
SUMMARY: Meta Platforms, the company formerly known as Facebook, has been sued for trademark infringement by MetaX LLC, a company that says it does business publicly as Meta and had been operating in the virtual and augmented reality technology space for years before Mark Zuckerberg announced his company's rebranding.

TITLE: DA moves to drop murder charge against bodega clerk who claimed self-defense in fatal stabbing
SUMMARY: The Manhattan District Attorney's Office filed a motion Tuesday to dismiss a murder charge against a bodega worker who fatally stabbed a man in what the employee's legal team argued was self-defense.

TITLE: First on CNN: Former Trump National Security Council official will testify at Thursday's January 6 hearing
SUMMARY: Matthew Pottinger, who served on former President Donald Trump's National Security Council before resigning in the immediate aftermath of January 6, 2021, will testify publicly at Thursday's prime-time hearing held by the House select committee investigating the US Capitol attack, according to multiple sources familiar with the plans.

TITLE: KFC just rolled out a new menu item to attract a younger crowd
SUMMARY: KFC is trying out a new type of chicken nugget in an effort to attract younger consumers.

TITLE: Ted Cruz says Supreme Court was 'clearly wrong' about 2015 same-sex marriage ruling
SUMMARY: Sen. Ted Cruz believes the US Supreme Court was "clearly wrong" in its landmark 2015 Obergefell v. Hodges ruling that legalized same-sex marriage, the Texas Republican said Saturday.

TITLE: Black executives' group jumps into secretary of state races and other down-ballot contests
SUMMARY: A version of this story appeared in the CITIZEN BY CNN newsletter. To get it in your inbox, sign up for free here.

TITLE: Putin arrives in Iran for first trip outside former Soviet Union since his invasion of Ukraine
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin arrived in Iran on Tuesday for his first international trip beyond the borders of the former Soviet Union since he launched Russia's invasion of Ukraine in February.

TITLE: More than 100 million in the US face excessive warning or heat advisories as a dangerous heat wave continues
SUMMARY: Heat alerts cover more than 20 states today and tomorrow across the Southern Plains and parts of the Northeast, and temperatures will soar above the century mark for 60 million people over the next week.

TITLE: Uvalde parents call for school board to fire district's police chief: 'Why the hell does he still have a job with y'all?'
SUMMARY: Angry residents of the emotionally shattered Texas town of Uvalde confronted the school board Monday night with speakers calling for district police chief Pedro "Pete" Arredondo to be fired and asking what safety measures will be put in place when schools reopen.

TITLE: Here's why Maryland's primary results may not be known for days
SUMMARY: It may take a few days, or even longer, to determine who will win Maryland's various primaries on Tuesday -- and that's because of how the state counts mail-in ballots.

TITLE: Opinion: Netflix's "Persuasion" is a work of sneaky genius
SUMMARY: Holly Thomas argues that Netflix's "Persuasion" is an Americanized pastiche of Regency England that couldn't be more perfectly designed to lure enraged viewers from Britain and wounded Austen fans from anywhere.

TITLE: Russian hackers behind SolarWinds breach continue to scour US and European organizations for intel, researchers say
SUMMARY: The Russian hackers behind a sweeping 2020 breach of US government networks have in recent months continued to hack US organizations to collect intelligence while also targeting an unnamed European government that is a NATO member, cybersecurity analysts tell CNN.

TITLE: Federal prosecutors won't pursue unlawful entry case against 'Late Show with Stephen Colbert' production team
SUMMARY: The US Attorney's Office for the District of Columbia will not prosecute members of a production team for "The Late Show with Stephen Colbert," after they were arrested last month by US Capitol Police as the team filmed a comedy segment at the US Capitol.

TITLE: How to keep your dog and other pets cool in the heat
SUMMARY: In the United Kingdom, where temperatures hit a record high on Tuesday, the Royal Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals and the British Veterinary Association recommend the following steps to keep your dog, cat or other animal safe during hot weather.

TITLE: January 6 committee chairman has Covid-19 but Thursday's hearing not impacted
SUMMARY: Democratic Rep. Bennie Thompson of Mississippi, chairman of the House select committee investigating the January 6, 2021, insurrection, has tested positive for Covid-19, his office announced Tuesday.

TITLE: Steve Bannon's trial begins
SUMMARY: Former Trump aide Steve Bannon is on trial on contempt of Congress charges for his failure to comply with a Jan. 6 House committee subpoena last year. Follow here for lives news updates.

TITLE: Sesame Place apologizes after character appears to ignore Black girls in viral video
SUMMARY: Sesame Place, a "Sesame Street" themed amusement park in Bucks County, Pennsylvania, is apologizing after a video shows a costumed character appearing to ignore two Black children during a parade on Saturday.

TITLE: UK workers suffer their biggest pay drop in two decades as inflation bites
SUMMARY: Workers in the United Kingdom are struggling with the biggest drop in pay in more than two decades, as surging food and energy prices take a giant bite out of wages.
